    "Here we use BERTScore (Zhang et al., 2020) for the similarity metric because of its robustness and high human correlation.",
    "Given the textual similarity scores between all reference and hypothesis nodes, we apply a bipartite matching solver in NetworkX foot_3 for nodes and obtain the nodes alignment between the reference and hypothesis graphs that are used for later evaluation.",
